# Feature Development Workflow

*This workflow defines the collaborative process between Development Team Lead (@DEV_LEAD) and DevOps Master (@GIT_MASTER) for feature development.*

## Roles & Responsibilities

### Development Team Lead (@DEV_LEAD)
- Feature planning and technical design
- Code implementation following vertical slice pattern
- Service layer business logic development
- API endpoint implementation
- Test implementation (unit + integration)
- Code quality enforcement (type hints, linting, async patterns)
- Architecture compliance verification
- Documentation updates

### DevOps Master (@GIT_MASTER)
- Git workflow management (branching, commits, PRs)
- CI/CD pipeline monitoring and troubleshooting
- GitHub issue/PR management
- Project board status updates
- Branch protection compliance
- Deployment readiness verification
- Infrastructure validation (storage, email services)

## Workflow Phases

### Phase 1: Pre-Development (Planning & Setup)

**Development Team Lead Tasks:**
1. Dependency Verification
   - Verify all infrastructure dependencies are complete
   - Confirm storage abstraction layer is available (`src/core/services/storage.py`)
   - Verify email service is available for notifications (`src/core/services/email.py`)
   - Check CORS configuration for public endpoints (`src/main.py`)

2. Feature Requirements Review
   - Review GitHub issue requirements
   - Review roadmap dependencies (`docs/ROADMAP.md`)
   - Review architecture decisions (`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`)
   - Review domain model (`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` - Database Schema)
   - Confirm model structures (`src/models.py`)

3. Technical Design
   - Design API endpoints (public vs authenticated)
   - Design service layer methods
   - Plan file upload handling (if needed)
   - Plan entity creation and relationships
   - Review existing schemas (`src/schemas.py`)

**DevOps Master Tasks:**
1. Project Board Management
   - Verify feature is in "Ready (MVP) 🎯" column
   - Move feature to "In Progress 🏗️" when development starts
   - Ensure previous feature is moved to "Done"

2. Issue Verification
   - Verify GitHub issue exists and is properly labeled
   - Confirm milestone is set correctly
   - Verify labels: `type,priority,scope` format

3. Branch Preparation
   - Verify `main` branch is up to date
   - Prepare branch naming: `feat/short-description`

### Phase 2: Development (Vertical Slice Implementation)

**Development Team Lead Tasks:**

**Step 1: Database Layer**
- Verify models exist (`src/models.py`)
- Create Alembic migration if schema changes needed
- Run migration: `alembic upgrade head`

**Step 2: Service Layer** (`src/services/`)
- Implement business logic methods
- Validate input data
- Handle file uploads via storage service (if needed)
- Create database records
- Send email notifications (via async task)
- Raise domain exceptions (`src/services/exceptions.py`)
- Follow async patterns (no blocking I/O)
- Add type hints to all functions

**Step 3: API Layer** (`src/api/`)
- Create endpoints (public or authenticated)
- Accept and validate requests using schemas
- Delegate to service layer
- Handle file uploads via storage service (if needed)
- Return appropriate HTTP responses
- Register router in `src/main.py`
- Add OpenAPI tags and descriptions

**Step 4: File Upload Handling** (if needed)
- Integrate with storage service (`src/core/services/storage.py`)
- Validate file type and size
- Store files using storage provider
- Update model fields with storage paths

**Step 5: Email Notifications** (if needed)
- Send emails via async task queue (`src/core/tasks.py::enqueue_email_task()`)
- Include relevant information in email

**DevOps Master Tasks:**
1. Branch Management
   - Create feature branch: `feat/short-description`
   - Ensure branch is based on latest `main`

2. CI/CD Monitoring
   - Monitor CI pipeline on each push
   - Verify linting passes (`ruff check`, `ruff format`)
   - Verify type hint validation passes
   - Verify blocking I/O validation passes
   - Verify test file validation passes
   - Troubleshoot any CI failures

3. Commit Standards
   - Ensure commits follow Conventional Commits format
   - Format: `feat(scope): description`
   - Keep commits atomic and focused

### Phase 3: Testing (Quality Assurance)

**Development Team Lead Tasks:**

**Service Layer Tests** (`tests/services/`)
- Test happy path scenarios
- Test file upload (if applicable)
- Test validation errors
- Test file validation (if applicable)
- Test entity creation
- Test email notifications (if applicable)
- Use `tests/conftest.py` for test fixtures
- Enable SQLite FK constraints in tests

**API Layer Tests** (`tests/api/`)
- Test endpoint success scenarios
- Test file upload (if applicable)
- Test input validation errors
- Test file type/size validation (if applicable)
- Test entity creation
- Test authentication/authorization (if applicable)

**Integration Tests**
- Test end-to-end flows
- Test storage integration (if applicable)
- Test email service integration (if applicable)

**DevOps Master Tasks:**
1. Test Execution
   - Run tests locally: `pytest -xvs`
   - Verify all tests pass before pushing
   - Monitor CI test execution
   - Ensure test coverage is adequate

2. Code Quality Checks
   - Verify linting passes: `ruff check .`
   - Verify formatting: `ruff format --check .`
   - Verify type hints: `python scripts/validate_type_hints.py`
   - Verify blocking I/O: `python scripts/validate_blocking_io.py`
   - Verify test files: `python scripts/validate_test_files.py`

### Phase 4: Code Review & Integration

**Development Team Lead Tasks:**
1. Pre-PR Checklist
   - All tests pass locally
   - Code follows project structure (`docs/CONTEXT.md`)
   - Service layer pattern followed (business logic in services)
   - No blocking I/O in async functions
   - All functions have type hints
   - Error handling implemented (domain exceptions)
   - Documentation updated if needed

2. Architecture Compliance
   - Vertical slice complete (DB → Service → API → Tests)
   - Admin as Gatekeeper: Public data requires admin approval
   - Hybrid Auth: Follow authentication model
   - Storage abstraction used (not direct file system access)
   - Email service used (async task queue)

**DevOps Master Tasks:**
1. Pull Request Creation
   - Use `gh pr create` with proper title and body
   - Link to GitHub issue using "Closes #123"
   - PR will auto-inherit milestone from linked issue
   - Assign to yourself: `--assignee "@me"`
   - Base branch: `main`

2. CI/CD Verification
   - Wait for CI to complete (lint, test, docker-build)
   - Verify all checks pass
   - Do NOT merge if CI fails
   - Fix any CI issues before requesting review

3. Project Board Update
   - Keep issue in "In Progress 🏗️" until PR is merged
   - Update issue with PR link

4. Merge Process
   - Wait for code review approval
   - Ensure branch is up to date with `main`
   - Merge using squash merge (trunk-based development)
   - Verify branch auto-deletes after merge

### Phase 5: Post-Development (Verification & Documentation)

**Development Team Lead Tasks:**
1. Feature Verification
   - Verify feature works end-to-end
   - Test file upload (if applicable)
   - Test email notification (if applicable)
   - Verify entity creation
   - Verify admin receives notifications (if applicable)

2. Documentation Updates
   - Update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` if architecture decisions made
   - Update API documentation if needed
   - Add code examples if complex logic

**DevOps Master Tasks:**
1. Project Board Finalization
   - Move feature from "In Progress 🏗️" to "Done"
   - Verify GitHub issue is closed
   - Update roadmap status if needed

2. Deployment Readiness
   - Verify Docker build succeeds
   - Verify health checks pass
   - Note: Actual deployment happens after MVP completion (per roadmap)

3. Dependency Unblocking
   - Verify dependent features' dependencies are met
   - Update project board if features can move to "Ready (MVP) 🎯"

## Critical Rules & Compliance

### Architecture Rules
- **Vertical Slice**: Complete end-to-end (DB → Service → API → Tests)
- **Admin as Gatekeeper**: Public data requires admin approval
- **Hybrid Auth**: Follow authentication model (Candidates are unauthenticated)
- **Storage Abstraction**: Use `src/core/services/storage.py`, not direct file system
- **Email Service**: Use async task queue, not blocking calls

### Code Quality Rules
- **Type Hints**: All public functions must have return type hints
- **Async Patterns**: No blocking I/O in async functions
- **Service Layer**: Business logic in services, routers are thin
- **Error Handling**: Domain exceptions, proper HTTP status codes
- **Testing**: Service tests + API tests, SQLite FK constraints enabled

### Git Workflow Rules
- **Branch Naming**: `feat/short-description`
- **Commits**: Conventional Commits format (`feat(scope): description`)
- **PR Requirements**: CI must pass, branch up to date, PR required
- **Merge Method**: Squash merge (trunk-based development)

### Project Board Rules
- **One Task at a Time**: Only one feature in "In Progress 🏗️"
- **Backend-First**: Complete backend API before frontend
- **Dependencies**: Verify all dependencies met before starting

